events.name: Western Kentucky Hilltoppers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Jonathan Taylor had two long touchdown runs, Alex Hornibrook threw for 257 yards and two scores and No. 4 Wisconsin opened the season with a 34-3 victory over Western Kentucky on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Taylor scores twice, No. 4 Wisconsin beats W. Kentucky

video.headline: Taylor finds daylight for 2nd TD of half

events.name: Utah State Aggies at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Connor Heyward scored his second touchdown with 2 minutes left to put No. 11 Michigan State ahead and the Spartans held on to beat Utah State 38-31 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heyward helps No. 11 Michigan State beat Utah State 38-31

video.headline: Heyward's late TD helps Michigan State avoid upset

events.name: San Diego State Aztecs at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: JJ Arcega-Whiteside caught three TD passes from K.J. Costello to overcome a slow night by Heisman Trophy runner-up Bryce Love and No. 13 Stanford opened the season with a 31-10 victory over San Diego State on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 13 Stanford beats San Diego St. 31-10 in season opener

video.headline: 80-yard TD catch puts Stanford ahead by two scores

events.name: Syracuse Orange at Western Michigan Broncos

headlines.description: Senior quarterback Eric Dungey rushed for 200 yards and passed for 184, coming back off the bench for Syracuse in a 55-42 win at Western Michigan on Friday in the season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dungey leads Syracuse over Western Michigan, 55-42

video.headline: Syracuse WR makes impressive one-handed catch and shakes defender for TD

events.name: Monmouth Hawks at Eastern Michigan Eagles

headlines.description: Tyler Wiegers and Mike Glass II threw two touchdown passes apiece, wideout Isaac Holder found Bryce Kemp on a flea-flicker and Eastern Michigan routed Monmouth (NJ) 51-17 on Friday night for its first-ever win against a Big South Conference team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Eastern Michigan downs Monmouth (NJ) 51-17 in opener

video.headline: Eastern Michigan QB throws 2nd TD to extend rout

events.name: Army Black Knights at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Daniel Jones threw for one touchdown and rushed for another score, helping Duke open with a 34-14 victory over Army on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones, Brown lead Duke past Army, 34-14, in opener

video.headline: Duke blocks FG and returns it into Army territory

events.name: Portland State Vikings at Nevada Wolf Pack

headlines.description: Ty Gangi threw three touchdown passes to McLane Mannix and Nevada cruised past FCS-member Portland State 72-19 on Friday night in a season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gangi, Mannix lead Nevada past Portland State 72-19

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Colorado State Rams

headlines.description: Steven Montez threw for 338 yards and four touchdowns, including an 89-yard strike to Laviska Shenault Jr. , as Colorado extended its win streak to four straight over Colorado State with a 45-13 rout on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colorado rolls to 4th straight win over Colorado State

video.headline: Colorado WR turns short pass into 89-yard TD
